sequenceDiagram
    participant Client as External Client
    participant Gateway as AI Gateway (Envoy)<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+
    participant ExtProc as ext_proc Filter<br/>9004/TCP gRPC plaintext
    participant MaasGuard as maas-headers-guard
    participant Resolver as model-provider-resolver
    participant Translation as api-translation
    participant KeyInject as apikey-injection
    participant NemoReq as nemo-request-guard<br/>(optional)
    participant K8sAPI as Kubernetes API<br/>443/TCP HTTPS mTLS
    participant NeMo as NeMo Guardrails<br/>HTTP (configurable)
    participant ExtSvc as ExternalName Service<br/>+ DestinationRule TLS
    participant Provider as External LLM Provider<br/>443/TCP HTTPS TLS 1.2+

    Note over Client,Provider: Flow 1: External Model Inference Request

    Client->>Gateway: POST /{ns}/{model}/v1/chat/completions<br/>Auth: Bearer Token (user)
    Gateway->>ExtProc: ext_proc request headers + body<br/>gRPC/9004 (plaintext, mesh-internal)

    rect rgb(230, 240, 255)
        Note over ExtProc,NemoReq: Plugin Pipeline (in-process)
        ExtProc->>MaasGuard: Process request
        MaasGuard->>MaasGuard: Strip x-maas-* headers<br/>Write originals to CycleState
        MaasGuard->>Resolver: Next plugin
        Resolver->>K8sAPI: Read ExternalModel/ExternalProvider<br/>(from in-memory cache)
        K8sAPI-->>Resolver: Model → Provider mapping
        Resolver->>Resolver: Write provider info to CycleState<br/>(endpoint, auth type, API format)
        Resolver->>Translation: Next plugin
        Translation->>Translation: Translate request body<br/>(e.g., OpenAI → Anthropic Messages API)
        Translation->>KeyInject: Next plugin
        KeyInject->>KeyInject: Read Secret from in-memory store<br/>Inject API key / SigV4 headers
        KeyInject->>NemoReq: Next plugin (if configured)
        NemoReq->>NeMo: POST /v1/guardrail/checks<br/>Input rails evaluation
        NeMo-->>NemoReq: Allowed / Blocked
        alt Blocked by NeMo
            NemoReq-->>ExtProc: 403 Forbidden
            ExtProc-->>Gateway: Reject request
            Gateway-->>Client: 403 Forbidden
        end
    end

    ExtProc-->>Gateway: Mutated headers + body

    Gateway->>ExtSvc: Forward via HTTPRoute<br/>TLS origination (DestinationRule SIMPLE)
    ExtSvc->>Provider: HTTPS/443<br/>Auth: Provider API key / SigV4

    Provider-->>ExtSvc: Inference response
    ExtSvc-->>Gateway: Response

    Gateway->>ExtProc: ext_proc response body<br/>gRPC/9004

    rect rgb(255, 240, 230)
        Note over ExtProc,NemoReq: Response Plugin Pipeline
        ExtProc->>Translation: Process response
        Translation->>Translation: Translate response body<br/>(e.g., Anthropic → OpenAI format)
        Translation->>NemoReq: Next plugin
        Note over NemoReq: nemo-response-guard evaluates output rails
    end

    ExtProc-->>Gateway: Mutated response body
    Gateway-->>Client: JSON Response<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS 1.2+

    Note over Client,Provider: Flow 2: ExternalProvider Reconciliation

    participant User as Platform Admin
    User->>K8sAPI: kubectl apply ExternalProvider CR<br/>HTTPS/443 TLS 1.2+

    rect rgb(230, 255, 230)
        Note over ExtProc,K8sAPI: ExternalProvider Controller
        K8sAPI-->>ExtProc: Watch event: ExternalProvider created
        ExtProc->>K8sAPI: Create ExternalName Service<br/>(maps provider name → FQDN)
        ExtProc->>K8sAPI: Create ServiceEntry<br/>(MESH_EXTERNAL, DNS resolution)
        ExtProc->>K8sAPI: Create DestinationRule<br/>(TLS origination mode: SIMPLE)
        ExtProc->>K8sAPI: Update ExternalProvider status → Ready
    end
